    Add mcp_bp package: hybrid BM25+semantic MCP server for Blueprint corpus
    
    Replaces the abandoned mcp/ prototype with a production-ready mcp_bp package.
    Key additions:
    
    - Hybrid search (hybrid_search.py): section-level BM25 via rank-bm25, optional
      fastembed semantic embeddings (BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5), fused with RRF.
      Enabled with BLUEPRINT_SEMANTIC_ENABLED=1; BM25-only by default.
    - New tools: get_blueprint_requirements (pillar-based requirement extraction),
      get_context_window (line-level context expansion), kb_stats (corpus stats).
    - ToolAnnotations (readOnlyHint, idempotentHint) on all tools.
    - ResourcesAsTools transform so clients without resource-protocol support
      (e.g. Claude Code) can access docs and Blueprint content via tools.
    - search_docs adds collection filter ("docs"/"prompts") and returns richer
      results: chunk_id, section_number, section_title, excerpt, rrf_score.
    - pyproject.toml: adds rank-bm25 and fastembed to the mcp optional extra.
    - 30 tests passing (9 new hybrid search tests).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

